diagnosis.final_diagnosis: Left ventricular to left atrial fistula due to traumatic mitral annular disruption
diagnosis.diagnostic_reasoning: The transesophageal echocardiogram revealed intact mitral leaflets but marked disruption and fistulization of the anterior mitral annulus, characterized by a 9 Ã— 7 mm irregular opening. The Doppler signal indicated mitral regurgitation. Given the history of trauma from a fall and absence of cardiovascular symptoms, the findings suggest an acquired defect rather than a primary valvular disease.
